<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="1412" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1412">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/308.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Spanish Ambassador</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Translations.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Spanish Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-02">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 2, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: I hasten to apprize your
                                excellency that I have received telegraphic instructions from the
                                Government of His Majesty the King, my August Sovereign, directing
                                me to apply to your excellency for your good offices to prevent the
                                Constitutionalists from enforcing the loan of 500,000 pesos they
                                demand of the Spaniards at Tampico.</p>
                            <p>I am carding out those instructions in asking that you will bring all
                                your influence to bear in order to prevent the consummation of this
                                fresh outrage on my fellow countrymen and I am sure that His
                                Majesty’s Government will highly appreciate such action as your
                                excellency may see fit to take to that end.</p>
                            <p>I avail [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Juan Riaño</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>